# Data Frame 2 or df2 is an aggregate data on facet total scores and over all total score, along with wealth and income data vs each response. 
# This data set is also sorted by income with all responses 'NA' removed.
# We also assign quartiles ranking each response according to this sort.

df4 = df2.sort_values(by = 'Q14. Income')
df4 = df4.reset_index(drop = True)
df4 = df4.dropna(axis = 0, subset = 'Q14. Income')
df4.insert(loc = len(df4.columns), column = "Quartile Number", value = pd.qcut(df4["Q14. Income"],q = 4, labels = False ) + 1, allow_duplicates = 'False')
